        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 5:02PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 502 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles northeast of Columbus, moving southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Afton and Aden Crater.

This includes Interstate 10 in New Mexico between mile markers 122
and 127.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
